subSubSection.paragraph:
NOTE. — Examination of two exuviae from consecutive molts of a juvenile female from ESEC Itirapina showed little variation in the spermathecae, even in size (
Fig. 6A, B
). The cephalothorax size of the exuvia of the first molt is 3.21 long; second molt, 4.46 long; the current size in life is 5.54 long.

HABITAT. — This species inhabits distinct environments, showing habitat plasticity (
Fig. 7
A-E). Specimens occurs in anthropized zones of seasonal forest (
Fig. 7A
), bordered in part by exotic 

Pinus

and 

Eucalyptus

forestry, as well in native savanna formations (
Fig. 7B
) at ESEC Itirapina (see 

Brasileiro 
et al.
2005

; 
IF 2006
for more details). At FLONA Ipanema, specimens occur in savanna formations within rock outcrops (
Fig. 7
C-D), bordered by seasonal forest (mostly Atlantic Forest (
Floresta Estacional semidecidual
), see 
Albuquerque & Rodrigues 2000
; 
IBAMA 2006
for more details) and anthropized areas (
Fig. 7E
). The species also occur in the city of 
São Paulo
, in a hygrophilous Atlantic Forest urban fragment; historically, this area had great influence and presence of savanna formations (
Hueck 1956
; 
Catharino & Aragaki 2008
), which could explain the spider’s current distribution in this more humid area.
